CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of Dr.
Richard Edward Landry.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To express sincere and heartfelt condolences of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the
3 passing of Dr. Richard Edward Landry and to commend and honor his life, legacy,
4 and service.
5 WHEREAS, it is with deep sorrow and profound regret that the members of the
6 Legislature of Louisiana recognize the passing of Dr. Richard Edward Landry on August 14,
7 2025, at the age of eighty-one; and
8 WHEREAS, Richard Landry was born on October 4, 1943, in Lake Charles,
9 Louisiana, to Lee and Willie Landry, and lived a life firmly rooted in the rich culture, faith,
10 and community spirit of Southwest Louisiana; and
11 WHEREAS, affectionately known as "Doc", he distinguished himself early as both
12 a student and athlete at Lake Charles High School, where he was a member of the 1958 State
13 Championship football team, learning lessons of discipline, teamwork, and perseverance that
14 would guide him throughout his life; and
15 WHEREAS, it was during his school years that he met Gaye Revelle, the love of his
16 life and steadfast partner of fifty-seven years, with whom he built a marriage grounded in
17 devotion, faith, and shared purpose; and
18 WHEREAS, Dr. Landry answered the call to serve his nation with courage and
