1 WHEREAS, his life stands as a testament to the enduring truth found in Scripture,
2 "Well done, good and faithful servant. You have been faithful over a little; I will set you
3 over much. Enter into the joy of your master" (Matthew 25:23), words that reflect the
4 faithful and servant-hearted life he so beautifully lived; and
5 WHEREAS, the people of Louisiana are richer for his presence and better for his
6 example, and his legacy will continue to inspire all who knew him.
7 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
8 commend and honor the life of Richard Edward Landry and does hereby recognize Dr.
9 Landry as a man of deep and abiding faith, a dedicated physician, a proud veteran, and a
10 beloved family man whose contributions to his community and his state will not be
11 forgotten.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby extend
13 sincere and heartfelt condolences to his wife, Gaye Revelle Landry, his children,
14 grandchildren, extended family, and all who were blessed to know him.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
16 family of Dr. Richard Edward Landry as an expression of enduring respect and sympathy.
